8.

\(h(x,n) = 1 + x + x^2 + \cdots + x^n = \sum_{i=0}^{n} x^i\)for\(h(x,n)\)\(h(0.3,55)\)

# h(x,n)
h <- function(x, n) {
  sum_result <- 0
  for (i in 0:n) {
    sum_result <- sum_result + x^i
  }
  return(sum_result)
}

# h(0.3,55)
result_h <- h(0.3, 55)
cat("h(0.3,55) =", result_h, "\n")
## h(0.3,55) = 1.428571

nn

List (c(1),c(1,1),c(1,2,1),c(1,3,3,1)) n

# 
generate_pascal_triangle <- function(n) {
  if (n <= 0) return(list())
  
  triangle <- list(c(1))
  
  for (i in 2:n) {
    prev_row <- triangle[[i-1]]
    new_row <- c(1)  # 1
    
    # 
    for (j in 2:i) {
      if (j <= length(prev_row)) {
        new_row <- c(new_row, prev_row[j-1] + prev_row[j])
      } else {
        new_row <- c(new_row, 1)  # 1
      }
    }
    
    triangle[[i]] <- new_row
  }
  
  return(triangle)
}

print_pascal_triangle <- function(triangle) {
  for (i in 1:length(triangle)) {
    spaces <- paste(rep(" ", length(triangle) - i), collapse = "")
    row <- paste(triangle[[i]], collapse = " ")
    cat(spaces, row, "\n")
  }
}
